# MongoDB Atlas (for live / cloud database)
# 1) Create free cluster: https://cloud.mongodb.com
# 2) Database Access → create user + password
# 3) Network Access → Add IP Address → Allow from Anywhere (0.0.0.0/0) for Render
# 4) Database → Connect → Drivers → copy connection string
# Example:
# MONGODB_URI=mongodb+srv://USER:PASSWORD@cluster0.xxxxx.mongodb.net/?appName=AKRentACar
# MONGODB_DB=ak_rent_a_car
#
# If MONGODB_URI is empty, the site uses local JSON files (for testing only).

MONGODB_URI=
MONGODB_DB=ak_rent_a_car
